BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

Variant isolates:

- Variant A: arrow system only. Lateral jog across waist (+/-2 px depending
  on lane), smaller arrowheads (base 3.5 / tip 6 vs V3b base 5 / tip 8),
  larger waist gap (y 55..104 and 136..185).
- Variant B: label system only. Vertical stagger for dual-top labels
  (left dy=3, right dy=8), ion vs word offsets (14 px vs 18 px),
  stoichiometry as compact superscript-style badge (anchor=end, font-size 11,
  at cx-4).
- Variant C: gradient dots only. Tight cluster near arrow lane with size/
  opacity gradient, tighter x territories (18..92 left, 310..384 right),
  pool rounded-rect background for clusters of three or more.
- Variant D: mechanism cues only. External-only arrows (no segment inside
  protein between y=108..132), central binding circle at (lane_x, 120),
  alternating-access double-arrow (approach + release).

Non-targeted dimensions fall back to the shared V3b sub.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

